  "texts": [
    "The role of action knowledge grows with the increase of iterations in self-learning.",
    "Figure 3 shows the ablation results about action knowledge on HotpotQA with Llama series models.",
    "Regardless of the number of iterations, the effect of using action knowledge (w/ action KB) is superior to that without action knowledge (w/o action KB).",
    "Another interesting finding is that as the number of iterations increases, the performance gap between w/o action KB and w/ action KB becomes more significant, indicating that the advantages of introducing action knowledge become more apparent.",
    "We consider that this can be attributed to the virtuous cycle between action knowledge and self-learning."
